task.summary: Default task

2.1.0
Update to fibers v0.6.8 for node v0.8 support.

2.1.4
Fix an instance of errors getting swallowed within nested asyncblocks.

2.1.6
Allow the current asyncblock's flow to be gotten from a function called from the current fiber.

2.1.7
* Fixing an issue with information getting lost when passing an object as an error to a callback waited on by asyncblock.

2.1.9
* Fix an issue with asyncblock incorrectly reporting line counts as being off in files that have the transformation code commented out.

2.1.10
* Fix a bug with flow.wait() interfering with defer()'d tasks

2.1.11
* Upgrading to fibers 1.0.0

2.1.12
* Just a version bump to trigger re-installing fibers for node v0.10.x
#20 - Don't use caller properties to support strict mode

2.1.13
Support strict mode
Adding some tests around throwing / catching errors
co poc

Simplifying code to pave the way for ES6 harmony generator support.
* Removed deprecated features (flow.func, asyncblock.wrap) * Removed flow.future and async().future() transform * Removed enumerator support
Updating benchmark script
Progress on harmony generator support
A little cleanup
More progress on generator support
Finished up error tests for generator support
Adding "waitless" yield syntax for generators
Progress towards replacing parser with Esprima (to support ES6 generator syntax)
